Day 9

Create a Simple HTML App and Dockerize It

📁 Step 1: Project Structure
Create a folder for your project:

my-html-app/
├── index.html
└── Dockerfile

📝 Step 2: Create index.html

<!-- index.html -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>My Dockerized App</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Hello from Docker!</h1>
  <p>This is a simple HTML app.</p>
</body>
</html>

🐳 Step 3: Create Dockerfile

# Use a lightweight web server
FROM nginx:alpine

# Remove the default nginx page
RUN rm -rf /usr/share/nginx/html/*

# Copy your HTML into the container
COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/

# Expose port 80
EXPOSE 80

🛠️ Step 4: Build the Docker Image

docker build -t my-html-app .

▶️ Step 5: Run the Container

docker run -d -p 8080:80 my-html-app

Now open your browser and go to:
👉 http://localhost:8080

You will see: "Hello from Docker!"

